# core keybindings
KEY1    KEY2    KEY3    DESCRIPTION
ESC                     exit the current mode, going up one level in the action stack, discarding any partial inputs
ENTER                   enter manual text editing mode when hovering over a passage, otherwise contextually trigger or send the selected action
CTRL    S               save current document
CTRL    SHIFT   S       save document and exit
CTRL    Q               exit, prompt for save if document has unsaved changes
CTRL    SHIFT   Q       autosave without prompt and exit immediatly
CTRL    F               find text all passages.
CTRL    SHIFT   F       find passage by searching through the associated raw user input text
TAB                     swap focus between passages or user input box
LEFT                    normal cursor position move in text edit mode, menu traversal when in a menu, when in passages mode opens left side menu options for current passage
RIGHT                   normal cursor position move in text edit mode, menu traversal when in a menu, when in passages mode opens right side menu options for current passage
UP                      normal cursor position move in text edit mode, menu traversal when in a menu, when in passages view moves focus to previous (upper) passage
DOWN                    normal cursor position move in text edit mode, menu traversal when in a menu, when in passages view moves focus to next (lower) passage
